This paper is about user intent detection in question-answering and dialog systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of capsule neural networks (CapsNet) suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which is commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the problem of zero-shot learning and knowledge transfer suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of real-world datasets suggests a potential focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
